Description: “A Sahrawi refugee woman walks amid the rubble of which were destroyed during heavy rain last year at the Samara refugee camp, west of the Algerian city of Tindouf in the disputed territory of Western Sahara,” Farouk Batiche (3/4/2016).

“Young Sahrawi refugees stand on the rubble of a house which was destroyed during heavy rain last year at the Boujdour refugee camp, near the Algerian city of Tindouf in the disputed territory of Western Sahara,” Farouk Batiche (3/3/2016).

“African migrants who were arrested in Algeria while illegally attempting to get to Europe, are seen in the refugee camp located in the Zeralda region, suburb of the city of Algiers in northern Algeria after Algerian government has started the process of expelling thousands of migrants,” Farouk Batiche (6/28/2018)
“Sahrawi children pose for a picture in the Smara refugee camp in Algeria's Tindouf province,” Farouk Batiche (2/25/2016)

“A Sahrawi refugee man rebuilds a house which was destroyed during heavy rain last year at the Samara refugee camp, west of the Algerian city of Tindouf in the disputed territory of Western Sahara,”  Farouk Batiche (3/4/2016).
“Indigenous Sahrawi girls play near their tent in a refugee camp of Al Smara in Tindouf, southern Algeria,” Zohra Bensemra (3/2/2016).
“An indigenous Sahrawi teacher attends a class at a school in a refugee camp of Boudjdour in Tindouf, southern Algeria,” Zohra Bensemra, (3/3/2016).
